  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Market Chain Interventions for Darjeeling Spice Producers</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Farmers</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mercy Corps&#x2019; Market Chain Intervention (MCI) project is an effort to revive the spice sectors in Darjeeling.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Project Goal: Provide spice farmers in northeast India with avenues to successfully enhance their own livelihoods. 

Activities: (1) Work with producers as well as middlemen, retailers, and wholesalers to improve the market chain through discussions, negotiations, collaborations, technical guidance, and financial support, (2) train farmers on improved techniques and systems for ginger farming based on the principles of organic agriculture, (3) provide loans to set up seed banks to provide cashless seed banking to ginger farmers, shielding them from fluctuating ginger prices and provide them with access to quality seeds, and (4), consolidate the market through extensive business planning and marketing</narrative>
  </description>
